biblesync
------------------------------------------
This is a C++ single class library encapsulating a protocol conduit. The
premise is that there is a local network over which to multicast Bible
navigation, and someone, possibly several someones, will transmit, and others
will receive. The choices for when you decide to xmit and what to do when you
recv are up to you as the application designer.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.4.1-1
  libbiblesync-devel-1.1.2+git20150102-1bl1
  libbiblesync1.1.2-1.1.2+git20150102-1bl1
  libgcc1-4.9.3-1
  libintl8-0.19.5.1-2
  libstdc++6-4.9.3-1
  libuuid1-2.25.2-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-4
  cmake-3.3.2-1
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.3-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/karlkleinpaste/biblesync

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/karlkleinpaste/biblesync.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack biblesync-1.1.2+git20150102-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./biblesync-1.1.2+git20150102-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/biblesync-1.1.2+git20150102-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/biblesync-1.1.2+git20150102-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbiblesync1.1.2-1.1.2+git20150102-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbiblesync-devel-1.1.2+git20150102-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

